Rating: 4
Have made this sauce before to serve with prime rib roast when tenderloin was cost prohibitive. (You won't even miss the au jus.) Definitely make the sauce ahead. I brown bacon in the oven, remove the bacon, and then add a bag of frozen pearl onions to the bacon grease and return to the oven to roast while the broth/port is reducing. Add the onions at the completion of the sauce so that it can absorb the flavors of the bacon and onions. (I don't add the bacon back in.) Prepare the roast using your favorite seasoning/roasting method and serve the sauce with or without the onions. When serving, I arrange them on the platter of sliced beef and guests can help themselves. This is impossible to screw up and the sauce is perfect every time. It is very versatile - a real hit with guests. Can't wait to try it with pork tenderloin as others have suggested.

