I cheated over christmas (hey I was hosting the in-laws for the first time!) and used grandma's standby: warm tenderloin to room temp, sprinkle w/s,p, and thyme, and roast in preheated oven @ 500 for 20 min. then turn down to 350 for another 15 min (or until thermometer says 125 in center). remove, spread w/butter, and cover w/foil for 10-15 min (this finishes the cooking up to med. rare for those of you doubting the 125 temp). yum! also, I have made the sauce both w/ and w/o bacon and it's always excellent. be sure to reduce fully to get the maximum flavor (and sneaking a spoonful of beef or veal demi-glace in never hurts either!). divine and perfect knock-their-socks-off food.

