I love this recipe and have made it several times. It has become a Christmas Eve tradition in our home. However, I have made some adjustments: I use half of the shallots called for in the recipe. I also make the entire sauce the day before, browning the bacon and adding to the sauce. I roast the meat separately, not browning in bacon grease as it doesn't need it. While the meat is roasting, I reheat the sauce and then strain the bacon and most of the shallots out of the sauce to make is a bit smoother. Spoon over the slices of meat for a lovely entree! I have also frozen any leftover sauce and served it over grilled beef fillet steaks and it's delicious!

