This was very good! I made for a dinner party and it was a big hit. I did simplify it a bit and like a few other reviewers I think you could easily skip the bacon and either use bacon drippings or oil to brown the meat. Instead of roasting the shallots I browned them in the same pan as the frying bacon peading things up a bit. I made the sauce as I prepared the meat and than did not add the drippings but just thickened it and added the shallots and bacon after it was reduced. This way I served my first course while the meat was roasting and as soon as the meat rested I was able to cut and serve as the sauce was all ready made. I also omitted the second 3 tbsp of butter from the sauce and it was delicious and plenty rich.

