Rating: 3
This WAS a delicious recipe! I recommend only 2 changes: (1) Use as many low-sodium sauce ingredients as you can, e.g. unsalted butter, low- or no-sodium beef broth (preferably organic, as the broth is the dominant flavor), don't salt the shallots, etc. The broth reduction + butter + bacon = a nearly-too-salty sauce, and you can always salt just before or after serving it. (2) I used a bit more flour in the butter/flour paste, and didn't add the second 3 T of butter (and didn't miss it at all). I served this roast with a potato/onion gratin, julienned squash/carrots, and some wonderful carmelized onion french bread (mmm, and tonight is leftovers!)

