Rating: 4
This is a FABulous dish!! It received rave reviews for Christmas dinner. Some changes: (1)I seared the tenderloin in bacon grease but did not use the bacon in the sauce--perfect bacon flavor that did not overwhelm the meat. (2) I only used 16 shallots and could have gotten away with less. They were $1.50 for 2 at my grocery store!! (3) I used 2-2.5 center cut tenderloins per the rec of my butcher. The amount was perfect for 10 people. Order the center cut loins rather than whole tenderloins to avoid the narrow, dry ends of the meat. This way, all the meat cooks evenly. (4) I used extra flour for a thicker sauce. (5) Served the meat from the kitchen rather than buffet style to avoid waste (another butcher rec.) Make the shallots and sauce a day ahead for time management. Also fry the bacon a day ahead and save the grease.

