I finally got around to making this after reading all the reviews. I thought it was excellent, and the sauce truly made the dish. Perhaps the reviewer who called the sauce "mundane" may not have been referring to the flavor, but perhaps that it is a fairly traditional sauce treatment. I did not use the butter/flour paste (buerre manie??) to thicken it, though. I prefer a thinner, closer to "jus" consistency for beef sauces. I used a little slurry made of cornstarch and a little red wine, and I added all the beef juice I collected from the "rested" tenderloin back to the sauce. It was lovely.

