Rating: 0
Wonderful for a Really Special occasion; in this case, my FIL's 75th birthday/my 10th anniversary. Be prepared to spend $$$. I bought $20/lb organic tenderloin, total $120 just for the meat. It was worth it. It takes longer than 30 minutes to brown the shallots and reduce the broth. When you're browning the tenderloin in a large roasting pan over two burners, the middle of the roasts won't get brown. You have to maneuver them around the pan to get them thoroughly brown. I made the roux in the saucepan using a little extra flour (about 2 t) while I was deglazing the roasting pan and boiling the broth, then added the broth to the roux. You don't need the extra 3T of butter. Forgot the watercress and didn't miss it. Horseradish mashed potatoes are the perfect side.

