Rating: 4
Outstanding. Two things make it even better: 1. Pepper the shallots HEAVILY before roasting; it helps give depth to the gravy and, 2. please don't skimp on your bacon, quantity and quality. Use a real quality bacon, not standard supermarket fare. You're spending around $100 between the beef and the port, an extra $15 for REAL bacon won't hurt. And cook a lot of it. One of the pleasures of preparing this meal is snacking on the crispy bacon pieces. You need to have some left for the gravy. Serve with baked sweet potatoes. Leftovers, over buttered egg noodles.

